        <h1>Forum Methods</h1>
        <p>All the below methods deal with reading and writing data related to the forum.</p>


        <h2>Methods to Get Information</h2>

        <h3>Reading the board List</h3>
        <dl>
            <dt>URI Format</dt><dd>forum</dd>
            <dt>Method</dt><dd>GET</dd>
            <dt>Authentication</dt><dd>No</dd>
        </dl>
        <p>Retrieves the list of all the forum boards. Output is an <a href="{{ path('_docs2_responses') }}#forum">forum list</a>.</p>

        <h3>Reading the topic List</h3>
        <dl>
            <dt>URI Format</dt><dd>forum/<em>id</em></dd>
            <dt>Method</dt><dd>GET</dd>
            <dt>Authentication</dt><dd>No</dd>
        </dl>
        <p>Retrieves the topic list of the specified by the id number. The output Output contains 2 objects called <code>pages</code> and <code>list</code>. The <code>list</code> object contains an arraylist of <a href="{{ path('_docs2_responses') }}#forum">forum models</a>. The <code>pages</code> object is an integer number which indicates the amount of pages.</p>
        <p>The values that can be sent in the get body:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><code>page</code>:  The current set of topics to return. Each set contains at most 20 items. Default value is &quot;1&quot; if not supplied.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Reading the sub board List</h3>
        <dl>
            <dt>URI Format</dt><dd>forum/board/<em>id</em></dd>
