        <h3>Searching the Forum</h3>
        <dl>
            <dt>URI Format</dt><dd>forum/search?<em>parameters</em></dd>
            <dt>Method</dt><dd>GET</dd>
            <dt>Authentication</dt><dd>No</dd>
        </dl>
        <p>Runs a search on the forum. Output is an <a href="{{ path('_docs2_responses') }}#forum">forum list</a>. Note that either the query or user parameter is required. All other parameters are optional.</p>
        <p>The following parameters are supported:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><code>query</code>: Keyword or phrase to search for. The minimum length is two characters, per MyAnimeList requirements. Phrases are searched literally.</li>
            <li><code>user</code>: A username of a user on MyAnimeList.</li>
            <li><code>userCategory</code>: An integer specifying how to search based on username. 1 will find posts made by the specified username, 2 will find topics/threads started by the specified username. Default value is 1. This value only has effect if a username is supplied.</li>
            <li><code>category</code>: An integer corresponding to the ID of a board to limit the search. Default is to search all boards.</li>
        </ul>


        <h2>Methods to Change Information</h2>

        <p class="alert alert-info">All post data <strong>must</strong> be sent as x-www-form-urlencoded as the API does not currently support multipart/form-data!</p>

        <h3>Adding Topics</h3>
        <dl>
            <dt>URI Format</dt><dd>forum/<em>id</em></dd>
            <dt>Method</dt><dd>POST</dd>
            <dt>Authentication</dt><dd>Required</dd>
        </dl>
        <p>Adds an topic to the specified board.</p>
        <p>The values that can be sent in the post body:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><code>title</code>: The title for the topic</li>
            <li><code>message</code>: The message for the topic.</li>
        </ul>

